HEADWORD: Sutural
<hw>Su"tur*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sutural</ets>, NL. <ets>suturals</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to a suture, or seam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Taking place at a suture; <as>as,
a <ex>sutural</ex> dehiscence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suturally</ent>⟦br⟧
